<Content>Fantastic!! We stayed here for three nights at the end of August and would thoroughly recommend this hotel in every respect. We had never visited Madrid before and so we could not have been more fortunate with the location of the hotel. Almost all of the major tourist sites were within a comfortable walk and the famous Madrid nightlife was literally on our doorstep.The hotel and, most importantly, the room were spotlessly clean and standards of housekeeping were very high throughout our stay. The bathroom and the furniture in the room were modern and more than adequate - certainly much better than the 3* rating might lead you to expect. We were on the first floor overlooking c/Victoria and, although it was fairly noisy in the evening and into the early hours, it was nothing that shutting the shutters and balcony windows (and a pair of ear plugs if you're a light sleeper), couldn't solve. Our room was also next to the lift but we heard no sound from it (or any other guests) the whole time we were there.Breakfast was a perfectly adequate continental affair, (although I failed to work out where the hot water for the decaf coffee sachets was kept). The staff - particularly those at Reception - were brilliant at all times. On our last night we managed to lose our key card but the lady on the desk sorted it out in no time at all. Incidentally, all the staff we met spoke very good English.We would certainly stay at this hotel again. A word of warning though - on our first night we failed to set an alarm. With the shutters and the curtains both closed the room was so dark that neither of us woke up until midday the following morning. This fact should also reassure any potential guests still worried about noise level at the hotel.Many thanks to the Victoria 4 for helping to make our first trip to Madrid so memorable!! 
