<Author>Englishtourists
<Content>Good location, well presented hotel My husband and I stayed at Hotel Victoria 4 in May 2007. We stayed in a room overlooking the street, Calle Victoria. We were pleased with our accomodation: the room was of a decent size and very clean. We were told by reception that the hotel had had a refit in 2005. The decor was very pleasant, or at least we thought so:: wood effect floors and magnolia walls with pleasant wood effect furnishings. The people at reception were very helpful and obliging.I would agree with comments I read about the hotel, prior to booking, with regard to the breakfast, which was included in the price we paid for the room. It wasn't particularly good, but of self service, canteen-style with hot drinks from a machine. Also, I had certain concerns re hygiene concerning the trays of food and tableware, guests might like to pay close attention to these and form their own opinion. However, we found that most hotels in Madrid did not include breakfast in the room rate, unlike the Victoria 4, also the hotel charges reasonable rates so we felt it was just as well to have breakfast elsewhere.The hotel is situated in a very convenient location in the old part of the city, within walking distant of most of the main tourist attractions, yet despite this it is not as noisy as we expected for such a central location. We had a very pleasant stay and would recommend this hotel. One word of caution: bag stealing and pickpocketing is rife in the area. My handbag was stolen from a bar opposite the hotel and two nights later we were having a meal in the outdoor paella restaurant that seems to be annexed to the hotel and a young lady on a nearby table had her handbag stolen. It really is not advisable to put a bag on the floor as it would seem that thieves are constantly on the lookout for the slightest opportunity to steal. 
