<Content>My new place to stay in Madrid I used to live in Madrid and went back to Spain for a vacation. We stayed at the Hotel Victoria 4 and thought it was great! The hotel has a classic look from the outside, but a sleek, modern look inside (Check out the circular bathroom in the middle of the lobby!)The staff were friendly and accomodating. I speak Spanish, but I heard them speaking English with other guests.The location can't be beat - it's 2 blocks from the Puerta del Sol (the center of Madrid), and surrounded by restaurants, great tapas bars, and cofee shops. The Prado is about a 15 minute walk, as is the Reina Sofia. The Plaza Mayor can be reached in about 10 minutes, and the Palacio Real in 15.The rooms were a nice size. At first we were given a cama matrimionial (two person bed), and when we asked for two separate beds, our room was changed immediately. We had a nice big window that opened to streets below. Once the window was closed, we couldn't hear any noise from the outside. Everything was immaculately clean, of course. Breakfast was included, consisting of the standards: coffee, juice, breads, ham, cheese, yogurt, cold cereals, fruit.Al in all, this is my new place to stay in Madrid. You will not be dissapointed. 
