<Content>Excellent all round, Me and partner have just returned from a 3 night stay at the Hotel Victoria 4, and we loved it! The location was spot on, very close to the Puerta de sol, but not right in so you do get some space around the hotel. (It's about 4-5 mins walk) If you're getting there, take the metro to Sol, it was so easy! First impressions of the hotel were great, the receptionist spoke very good English and checked us in quickly. Our room was on the 5th floor , so we had a view over rooftops but this wasnt important, the room was pretty big, was very very clean, and looked very swanky with wooden floors. It was also pretty quiet! The room had a table and chairs towards the window, so you could relax away from the bed, and a great little minibar thatw as stocked each day. The bathroom was stoned/marbled , again very clean and the shower/bath was a good size. It was definitely one of the best hotels I have stayed at(admittedly that is limited) but for 3* you won't go wrong if you stay here. Highly recommended. 
