<Content>Great location and Very good value Just back from 5 nights with 2 rooms at this hotel. We had read the recent reviews and they are pretty accurate. The location is very brilliantly central ( you can go back to the hotel in the heat of the day) and the rooms are very clean and good value. We stayed on the fifth floor which only had views over the rooftops. The good point was this made it quiet as many rooms overlook the street restaurant (all appear double glazed though). Other low spots were the wooden floored corridors (quite noisy footsteps by) but not as bad as we expected from the other reviews. The terrace referred to in hotel literature is open but there were no chairs on it! The hotel staff were all really helpful and booked us coach tickets. We booked on lastminute .com and the tariff included breakfast. The breakfast is fine for a continental breakfast but not too much variety over our 5 days. Having said the rooms were very clean you find the odd chipped plate but we found these in much better Madrid restaurants. We recommend the metro one euro from the airport, the Telefonica cable ride for less than 5 euro return, visit a bullfight on sunday (I think they end in october) see a soccer match Athletico or Real Madrid, see a Flamenco dance. Last tip : each restaurant is obliged to offer a menu of the day but they dont show you it until you ask. 
