<Content>Good hotel, central location This hotel has a great location, 5 minutes walk from the main shopping area, historical Plaza Mayor and metro links. We couldn't fault the friendliness and helpfulness of the staff during our stay. Our room was clean and had everything we needed for a 2 night stay, the bed was comfortable, the shower was lovely and the air conditioning was fantastic (just make sure to turn it up at night because it was a little too cold when we didn't!). The breakfast was really good with fresh bread/croissants and cereals etc (perhaps this has improved since the reviews written about the bad breakfast that we read on trip advisor before we went). The only downfall of our stay was being disturbed by street noise at night (this was probably made worse because we had a front-facing room). All in all we would recommend this hotel, you couldn't beat the price when we looked around for similar hotels and it lived up to the other reviews we had read before booking it. 
